Introduction

Park Jae-hyung, known professionally as Jae and eaJ, is a South Korean-American musician, singer, and songwriter. He was the lead vocalist and lead guitarist of the rock band DAY6 under JYP Entertainment before his departure in 2022.

Before debuting with DAY6, Jae gained recognition as a top-six finalist on the first season of the SBS survival program K-pop Star. He officially debuted with DAY6 on September 7, 2015, with the album "The Day."

In 2020, he began releasing solo music under the name eaJ, showcasing a different musical style. On January 1, 2022, JYP Entertainment announced the termination of his contract, confirming his departure from both the group and the company. Since then, Jae has continued his solo career independently.
